<!-- We need a doctype to allow us to use special characters like &nbsp;
     We use a "strict" DTD to make IE follow the alignment rules. -->

<html xmlns:t="http://tapestry.apache.org/schema/tapestry_5_4.xsd">
<body class="container">
    <h3>Styled Grid</h3>

    By default, Grid emits the BootStrap classes <code>table table-hover table-bordered table-striped</code>.
    To override this styling, either override the CSS of those classes or, as we have done here, specify the classes you want.

    <div class="eg">
        <t:grid source="persons" rowsPerPage="4" pagerPosition="top" class="table table-bordered"/>
    </div>

    References:
    <a href="http://getbootstrap.com/css/#tables">.table</a>,
    <a href="http://tapestry.apache.org/5.4/apidocs/org/apache/tapestry5/corelib/components/Grid.html">Grid</a>.<br/><br/>

    <t:pagelink page="Index">Home</t:pagelink><br/><br/>

    The source for IPersonFinderServiceLocal and @EJB is shown in the Session Beans and @EJB examples.<br/><br/>
</body>
</html>